pera.it/archives/category/recensioni/" >Opera</a> </span> <span class="meta-author" title="Author"> <i class="icon-user"></i> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://www.gbopera.it/author/charliese-tee/" title="View all posts by Charlise Tiee" rel="author">Charlise Tiee</a></span> </span> <span class="meta-tags" title="Tags"> <i class="icon-tags"></i> <a href="http://www.gbopera.it/tag/david-daniels/" rel="tag">David Daniels</a>, <a href="http://www.gbopera.it/tag/david-mcvicar/" rel="tag">David McVicar</a>, <a href="http://www.gbopera.it/tag/diana-damrau/" rel="tag">Diana Damrau</a>, <a href="http://www.gbopera.it/tag/dmitri-hvorostovsky/" rel="tag">Dmitri Hvorostovsky</a>, <a href="http://www.gbopera.it/tag/dolora-zaijck/" rel="tag">Dolora Zaijck</a>, <a href="http://www.gbopera.it/tag/fabio-luisi/" rel="tag">Fabio Luisi</a>, <a href="http://www.gbopera.it/tag/giuseppe-filianoti/" rel="tag">Giuseppe Filianoti</a>, <a href="http://www.gbopera.it/tag/gluck/" rel="tag">Gluck</a>, <a href="http://www.gbopera.it/tag/il-trovatore/" rel="tag">Il Trovatore</a>, <a href="http://www.gbopera.it/tag/kate-royal-lisette-oropesa/" rel="tag">Kate Royal. Lisette Oropesa</a>, <a href="http://www.gbopera.it/tag/marcelo-alvarez/" rel="tag">Marcelo Alvarez</a>, <a href="http://www.gbopera.it/tag/marco-armiliato/" rel="tag">Marco Armiliato</a>, <a href="http://www.gbopera.it/tag/nancy-fabiola-herrera/" rel="tag">Nancy Fabiola Herrera</a>, <a href="http://www.gbopera.it/tag/opera-lirica/" rel="tag">Opera lirica</a>, <a href="http://www.gbopera.it/tag/orfeo-ed-euridice/" rel="tag">Orfeo ed Euridice</a>, <a href="http://www.gbopera.it/tag/sondra-rdvanovsky/" rel="tag">Sondra Rdvanovsky</a>, <a href="http://www.gbopera.it/tag/stefan-kocan/" rel="tag">Stefan Kocan</a>, <a href="http://www.gbopera.it/tag/verdi/" rel="tag">Verdi</a><meta itemprop="keywords" content="David Daniels, David McVicar, Diana Damrau, Dmitri Hvorostovsky, Dolora Zaijck, Fabio Luisi, Giuseppe Filianoti, Gluck, Il Trovatore, Kate Royal. Lisette Oropesa, Marcelo Alvarez, Marco Armiliato, Nancy Fabiola Herrera, Opera lirica, Orfeo ed Euridice, Sondra Rdvanovsky, Stefan Kocan, Verdi"> </span> </footer></div> </article><div id="author-block" class="box-shadow-2px clearfix" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"><h2 class="author-title">About the author</h2><div id="author-avatar"> <img itemprop="image" style="display:none;" src="http://gravatar.com/avatar/f7ee7f5b7b23d22ae54a434de6327558" alt="" /> <img src="http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/f7ee7f5b7b23d22ae54a434de6327558?s=100&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g" width="100" height="100" alt="" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 photo avatar-default" /></div><div id="author-description" class="padding-20"><meta itemprop="name" content="Charlise Tiee"><meta itemprop="url" content=""><p></p><p class="add-author-info"> <a href="#"><i class="icon-facebook-sign"></i></a><a href="#"><i class="icon-twitter-sign"></i></a><a href="#"><i class="icon-google-plus-sign"></i></a></p> <a style="font-size: 11px;" href="http://www.gbopera.it/author/charliese-tee/">View all articles by Charlise Tiee</a></div></div><div class="nav-block box-shadow-2px padding-20 clearfix"> <nav class="nav-single"><h3 class="assistive-text">Post navigation</h3> <span class="nav-previous"><a href="http://www.gbopera.it/2011/05/torino-teatro-regiorigoletto/" rel="prev"><span class="meta-nav">&larr;</span> Torino, Teatro Regio:&#8221;Rigoletto&#8221;</a></span> <span class="nav-next"><a href="http://www.gbopera.it/2011/05/pierre-alexandre-monsigny-1729-1817le-deserteur/" rel="next">Pierre-Alexandre Monsigny (1729-1817):&#8221;Le Dserteur&#8221; <span class="meta-nav">&rarr;</span></a></span> </nav><nav class="nav-single-hidden"> <span class="nav-previous"></span> <span class="nav-next"></span><div class="clear"></div> </nav></div><div class="comments-block box-shadow-2px clearfix"><div id="comments" class="comments-area"><h2 class="comments-title"> 1 comment</h2><ol class="commentlist"><li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-14960"> <article id="comment-14960" class="comment clearfix"> <header class="comment-meta comment-author vcard"><div class="comment-avatar"><img src="http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/f7bb4f65f3b7a3d5562bcbd39e469660?s=75&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g" width="75" height="75" alt="" class="avatar avatar-75wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-75 alignnone photo avatar-default" /></div><cite class="fn">Lisen Hillestad</cite><a class="comment-meta-time muted-small" href="http://www.gbopera.it/2011/05/metropolitan-operaorfeo-ed-euridice-il-trovatore-rigoletto/#comment-14960"><time datetime="2012-02-28T15:19:33+00:00">28 febbraio 2012 at 15:19</time></a> </header> <section class="comment-content comment"><p>I watched the HD transfer of Il Trovatore from the Met and now once again on TV.  I think there was plenty to enjoy, but strangely, in spite of quite a brisk pace and very experienced singers, the performance for me was somewhat short of  inner tension, a &#8220;nerve&#8221;.  Hvorostovsky has a stunning voice and ditto looks  but I got a slight impression that he was a bit uninspired.  He did not really take fire. Perhaps his mood that day was too happy (his parents watched him in HD transfer for the first time!).  As to Alvarez, I agree with the reviewer that he showed no trace of heroism, yes, he was &#8220;lamentoso&#8221;, even presenting some histrionics. But his acting was intense and well, energetic: He expressed the poor man&#8217;s desperation in a quite physical way, looking somewhat savage from time to time.  But I enjoyed his singing. &#8211; To me, the real star of the evening was Sondra Radvanovsky, presenting a full, rich voice on all levels, beautiful piano passages as well as forte, e real Verdian soprano.  I wish they had cast her for Ernani &#8230;  At the other end of the scale:  the Azucena of Dolora Zajick.  Her wooden face and complete lack  of energy, feeling, emotion in singing and acting made her one of the most unsatisfying Azucenas I have seen, and unpleasant to watch.  A&#8217;s obsession for revenge is so necessary for the plot and to give the piece a minimum of credibility (!), but Zajick does not succeed in making this spring to life.</p> </section><div class="reply clearfix"></div> </article></li></ol><div id="respond" class="comment-respond"><h3 id="reply-title" class="comment-reply-title">Lascia un commento <small><a rel="nofollow" id="cancel-comment-reply-link" href="/2011/05/metropolitan-operaorfeo-ed-euridice-il-trovatore-rigoletto/#respond" style="display:none;">Annulla risposta</a></small></h3><form action="http://www.gbopera.it/wp-comments-post.php" method="post" id="commentform" class="comment-form"><p class="comment-notes"><span id="email-notes">Il tuo indirizzo email non sar pubblicato.</span> I campi obbligatori sono contrassegnati <span class="required">*</span></p><p class="comment-form-comment"><label for="comment">Commento</label><textarea id="comment" name="comment" cols="45" rows="8" maxlength="65525" aria-required="true" required="required"></textarea></p><p class="comment-form-author"><label for="author">Nome <span class="required">*</span></label> <input id="author" name="author" type="text" value="" size="30" maxlength="245" aria-required=\'true\' required=\'required\' /></p><p class="comment-form-email"><label for="email">Email <span class="required">*</span></label> <input id="email" name="email" type="text" value="" size="30" maxlength="100" aria-describedby="email-notes" aria-required=\'true\' required=\'required\' /></p><p class="comment-form-url"><label for="url">Sito web</label> <input id="url" name="url" type="text" value="" size="30" maxlength="200" /></p><p class="form-submit"><input name="submit" type="submit" id="submit" class="submit" value="Commento all&#039;articolo" /> <input type=\'hidden\' name=\'comment_post_ID\' value=\'16936\' id=\'comment_post_ID\' /> <input type=\'hidd